ALC Communications Corp saidthat because of strong traffic growth and cost reductions itanticipates reporting a profit for the first quarter of 1987,versus a loss of 1.4 mln dlrs, or 15 cts a share, for the firstquarter of 1986.    Earlier, the company reported a net after-tax loss for 1986of 60.8 mln dlrs, or 4.63 dlrs a share, compared with a loss of28.9 mln dlrs, or 2.43 dlrs a share, in 1985.    Reuter&#3;